cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NI 

This paper deals with frequency hopping sequences and their correlation properties, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of trace functions and discrete logarithm also suggests a connection to number theory and algebraic structures, which are relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the study of synchronization and multiple-access systems falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
